<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>get on the bandwagon • go on the wagon</xh5><p> <i>get on the bandwagon—</i>join in what seems likely to be a successful enterprise (in the hope of a personal gain): Once it was clear that he would be elected, all the uncommitted politicians tried to <u>get on the bandwagon</u>.</p><p> <i>go on the wagon—</i>intend not to drink any alcohol at all: Carter says that he is really serious this time about <u>going on the wagon</u>.</p> </entry>
